[Gentle music]

57
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:30,250
[Billiard balls clacking]

58
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:35,300
- You cheat.

59
00:03:37,210 --> 00:03:39,340
- With you, I don't have to.

60
00:03:40,350 --> 00:03:43,090
[Upbeat music]

61
00:03:43,170 --> 00:03:45,310
- Now, chain of command.

62
00:03:45,390 --> 00:03:48,090
General, colonel,
major, captain-

63
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:49,570
- I know the chain of command.

64
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:51,010
The exam hardly matters, anyway,

65
00:03:51,090 --> 00:03:53,140
it's the vote that counts.

66
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:55,010
- Easy, nurse, easy.

67
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,620
He'll be back.

68
00:03:56,710 --> 00:03:58,010
- After the vote you'll be
calling me, captain Healy.

69
00:03:58,100 --> 00:03:59,230
Don't you forget it.

70
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:01,410
- I'll be calling you mudsill.

71
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,280
[Upbeat music]

72
00:04:12,550 --> 00:04:15,470
[Grass rustling]

73
00:04:15,550 --> 00:04:18,950
- Is this what you're meant
to be doing right now?

74
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,080
How long have you
spent with this?

75
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:22,260
How long have you been idle

76
00:04:22,340 --> 00:04:24,390
while your sister sweats?

77
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:28,260
- She told me to
learn these words-

78
00:04:28,350 --> 00:04:30,870
- and what am I telling you now?

79
00:04:32,610 --> 00:04:35,530
Ever since you've got those
specs, you've been useless.

80
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:37,230
We need a man on this farm,

81
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:39,580
not a child, wearing these.

82
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,280
- Please.

83
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,190
- You were more useful when
you were slow and dumb.

84
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:48,150
What should we do
about that now?

85
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,330
You read that book didn't you?

86
00:04:50,420 --> 00:04:52,810
If your right arm
causes you to sin,

87
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:53,680
cut it off.

88
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:58,340
If your right eye
causes you to sin,

89
00:04:58,420 --> 00:05:02,300
put it out and you
will stop sinning.

90
00:05:02,380 --> 00:05:03,170
- Please.

91
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:07,820
[Younger sister yells]

92
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:12,440
[Girls gasping]

93
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,060
[Dramatic music]

94
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,410
- [Older sister] You!

95
00:05:32,410 --> 00:05:35,240
[Frantic music]

96
00:06:00,270 --> 00:06:02,660
[Both gasping]

97
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:09,360
[Muffled talking]

98
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:22,160
[Boom vibrates]

99
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,510
[Heartbeat thudding]

100
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:26,420
[Boom vibrates]

101
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:33,340
[Muffled talking]
[Heartbeat thudding]

102
00:06:39,220 --> 00:06:40,790
[Bell ringing]

103
00:06:40,870 --> 00:06:42,270
[Men laughing]

104
00:06:42,350 --> 00:06:43,790
- Boys, boys, what
are you doing here?

105
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,360
- Where's our young captain?

106
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,400
- Gotta run him in.

107
00:06:46,490 --> 00:06:48,450
- The exam, boys, exam.

108
00:06:49,710 --> 00:06:53,320
- Exam, he could fold it up
and put it under his hat.

109
00:06:53,410 --> 00:06:54,890
- In, all of you.

110
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:58,240
[Billiard balls clacking]
[Men laughing]

111
00:06:58,330 --> 00:06:59,810
- [Man] I hope you boys

112
00:06:59,890 --> 00:07:01,240
don't shoot like this
on the battlefield.

113
00:07:01,330 --> 00:07:04,070
- [Soldier] Don't you
single me out, cross eyes.

114
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:06,030
- Miss, you sure
he's not back yet?

115
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:08,940
- [Soldier] I'm getting tired
of this mob of blind men.

116
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:10,120
You couldn't hit water
if you fell off a boat.

117
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:11,470
- [Soldier] Woohoo.

118
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,820
- [Soldier]
Gentlemen, button it.

119
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,260
- Yeah!
- Let her go.

120
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:21,300
- Yeah.
- Nice, very nice.

121
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,440
- [Man] Very nice.

122
00:07:26,530 --> 00:07:27,790
- [Soldier] Oh, excellent.

123
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:28,620
- [Man] Good going.

124
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,400
[Men laughing]

125
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:31,750
Very nice shot.

126
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:37,360
- Yeah, yeah.
- Good shot.

127
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:38,230
Good shot.

128
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:39,630
- Yeah.
- Um-hm.

129
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:49,460
[Men chuckling]
[Men murmuring]

130
00:07:56,340 --> 00:07:57,990
- [Nurse] Miss, miss.

131
00:07:59,170 --> 00:08:01,260
- [Alan's sister] Listen to her.

132
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:03,480
Begging your pardon, boys.

133
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,610
I'll be back in a minute.

134
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:10,530
- [Man] How about leaving
some for the rest of US?

135
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:12,920
- What the devil are you doing?

136
00:08:13,010 --> 00:08:15,400
- [Scoffs] They just needed
a halfway decent shot.

137
00:08:15,490 --> 00:08:17,320
- They're voting on your
brother's officership

138
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,410
here in a few hours.

139
00:08:18,490 --> 00:08:20,760
You are embarrassing them.

140
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:24,370
- We have known these
boys for years, years.

141
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:26,460
Oh, run along and
get a drink of water.

142
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:28,630
You'll feel much better.

143
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,160
- [Father] Voted down!

144
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,720
- [Alan] That's what
happened, father.

145
00:08:31,810 --> 00:08:32,850
- [Father] How in heaven's name

146
00:08:32,940 --> 00:08:34,810
could you have been voted down?

147
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:35,860
- Honestly, I don't know.

148
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:37,470
We were all chums this morning

149
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:39,510
and then now they don't
want anything to do with me.

150
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,340
- [Father] This is
a devil of a fix.

151
00:08:41,430 --> 00:08:44,520
I refuse to have a son
at home, out of uniform.

152
00:08:44,610 --> 00:08:45,950
- You won't.

153
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,350
I walked down the
street and enlisted.

154
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,570
- [Father] Enlisted?

155
00:08:49,650 --> 00:08:51,390
As a private?

156
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,700
- I ship out tomorrow.

157
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:54,530
- [Father] You will withdraw it.

158
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:56,440
- [Alan] I can't withdraw it.

159
00:08:56,530 --> 00:08:57,660
- [Father] This has
beneath your station

160
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:59,400
and beneath your prospects.

161
00:08:59,490 --> 00:09:01,490
You have responsibilities
to your family

162
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,800
and your class.

163
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,150
- [Alan]
Responsibilities to what?

164
00:09:04,230 --> 00:09:06,190
Sit out the war
on a feather bed?

165
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:09,110
[Foreboding music]

166
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:21,990
[Footsteps clomping]

167
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,080
- You, up.

168
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,910
Bring him back!

169
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:32,220
[Upbeat banjo music]
[Men chattering]

170
00:09:32,310 --> 00:09:33,090
- [Soldier] Attention.

171
00:09:33,180 --> 00:09:36,140
[Soldiers chanting]

172
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:53,890
[Soldiers yelling orders]

173
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:12,040
- Go on, girl.

174
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:19,920
[Clock ticking]

175
00:10:31,450 --> 00:10:34,450
- The next meeting is on Monday.

176
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:36,500
- My brother ships out tomorrow.

177
00:10:36,590 --> 00:10:37,720
- I had heard.

178
00:10:39,890 --> 00:10:41,550
I'm going with him.

179
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:48,690
When I was nine you told me

180
00:10:48,770 --> 00:10:51,380
you knew when I was fooling.

181
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:53,130
Am I fooling now?

182
00:10:53,210 --> 00:10:54,130
You tell me.

183
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,560
You can tell me
what I'm going into

184
00:10:57,650 --> 00:11:00,570
or I can find out on my own.

185
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:01,740
I am not afraid.

186
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:11,190
- The nearest term for what
you are now is vivandiere.

187
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:15,150
This is not like
in the operettas.

188
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:18,500
There are no sanitary
commissions where you're going.

189
00:11:18,590 --> 00:11:21,590
There are no respectable ladies.

190
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,590
You march as the men do.

191
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,640
You eat as they do.

192
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,380
You sleep as they do.

193
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:30,420
You are a camp follower.

194
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:32,860
[Clock ticking]

195
00:11:32,950 --> 00:11:35,600
[Gentle music]

196
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:38,950
You're not an official
part of the army.

197
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:41,430
You receive neither rank nor pay

198
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:44,050
nor even the clothes
on your back.

199
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:47,530
Anything you have, you
have by scrounging, begging

200
00:11:47,610 --> 00:11:48,830
or bringing it with you.

201
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:51,570
[Somber music]

202
00:12:27,610 --> 00:12:29,790
[She sighs]

203
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:50,810
[Father wheezing]

204
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:01,780
You are at the mercy
of the officers.

205
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:06,080
They can expel you from camp
at any time far from home.

206
00:13:06,170 --> 00:13:09,650
Your only hope is to
make yourself necessary.

207
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:12,920
[Soldiers chattering]

208
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:25,800
- Come with me.

209
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:34,810
[Man coughing]
[Soldier groaning]

210
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:42,860
- [Wounded soldier] Please,
please, god, please.

211
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:47,470
[Soldier coughing]

212
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:55,390
[Flies buzzing]

213
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:05,880
[Soldiers chattering]

214
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:13,240
[He sighs]

215
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:19,680
You have a bedroll?

216
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:23,990
One'll open up soon.

217
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:26,470
- No, it will not, steward.

218
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,820
I will not have
women in this camp.

219
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:31,730
I will not have children here.

220
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:33,520
Now, you instruct her to leave

221
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:37,000
or the provost marshal
will perform that duty.

222
00:14:37,090 --> 00:14:39,920
- You look a little
peckish, colonel.

223
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,480
You need another
day in the hospital.

224
00:14:42,570 --> 00:14:45,620
- I am needed till
midday at the latest.

225
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:47,230
- And make it two to be safe.

226
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,660
- I will walk out of here

227
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:51,450
if I have to write
Jeff Davis himself.

228
00:14:51,540 --> 00:14:53,930
- You care to make it three?

229
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:56,110
- Ah, devil take you, steward.

230
00:14:56,190 --> 00:14:58,240
[Colonel groans]

231
00:14:58,330 --> 00:15:01,110
- You look better
already, colonel.

232
00:15:05,990 --> 00:15:08,900
[Melancholy music]

233
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:33,010
[Soldier winces]

234
00:15:45,630 --> 00:15:48,030
[Somber music]

235
00:15:52,290 --> 00:15:54,990
[Gentle music]

236
00:16:00,780 --> 00:16:04,260
- [Mrs. Fultz] You will
face danger without defense.

237
00:16:04,350 --> 00:16:08,270
You are there as an angel
of mercy, never vengeance.

238
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:10,360
You move above the fray.

239
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:12,620
So understand this.

240
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:15,320
[Steamboat whistle blowing]
[Soldiers chattering]

241
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:18,670
You are never, ever
to join the fight.

242
00:16:20,190 --> 00:16:24,720
♪ We are a band of brothers
and native to the soil ♪

243
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:28,810
♪ fighting for the property
we gained by honest toil ♪

244
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:32,550
♪ hurrah, for the Bonnie blue
flag that bears a single star ♪

245
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:35,290
[Crowd cheering]

246
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:39,910
♪ Hurrah, for the
Bonnie blue flag ♪

247
00:16:39,990 --> 00:16:43,130
[Train wheels clacking]

248
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,040
- [Man] Hey.

249
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:51,740
[Solders chattering]

250
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:03,800
[People yelling]
[Guns firing]

251
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:07,330
[Artillery shell explodes]

252
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:19,120
[Muffled heartbeat pounding]

253
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:23,040
[Vivandiere pants]

254
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:28,090
[Men yelling]
[Guns firing]

255
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:33,960
[Vivandiere hyperventilates]

256
00:17:34,050 --> 00:17:35,530
- [Solider] Sir, if
they reload that Cannon.

257
00:17:35,610 --> 00:17:36,880
- I understand.

258
00:17:41,010 --> 00:17:41,920
- Take 'em.

259
00:17:48,450 --> 00:17:49,630
[Guns firing]

260
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:52,110
[Somber music]

261
00:18:00,070 --> 00:18:03,120
[Heartbeat pounding]

262
00:18:12,130 --> 00:18:13,700
[Vivandiere gasps]

263
00:18:13,780 --> 00:18:16,660
[Melancholy music]

264
00:18:26,490 --> 00:18:29,150
[Water sloshing]

265
00:18:31,020 --> 00:18:33,890
[Vivandiere cries]

