00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:21,260
[Men chuckling]
[Men clapping]

291
00:20:30,050 --> 00:20:32,360
[Men yelling]

292
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:34,880
- [Soldier] Hello, anyone there?

293
00:20:34,970 --> 00:20:37,710
[Healy's sister moans]

294
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:41,190
[Water sloshing]

295
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:44,190
[Gentle music]

296
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:49,200
[Thunder roaring]
[Rain pattering]

297
00:20:51,420 --> 00:20:54,070
[Gentle music]

298
00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:28,540
[Vivandiere sniffles]

299
00:21:28,630 --> 00:21:30,110
- [Soldier] Hey.

300
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,590
The colonel needs help
and the surgeon's busy.

301
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:32,420
Come on.

302
00:21:38,420 --> 00:21:40,120
- We hold a service
another hour,

303
00:21:40,210 --> 00:21:43,120
rains made any
bearing slow going.

304
00:21:43,210 --> 00:21:44,430
- I expect.

305
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:46,520
- There's also the matter of

306
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,260
this creature on the loose.

307
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:50,350
This man, gunner foucher.

308
00:21:51,350 --> 00:21:53,000
- Partisan ranger?

309
00:21:53,090 --> 00:21:55,220
- No, sir, the grave robber.

310
00:21:55,310 --> 00:21:56,310
[Bell rings]

311
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,140
- Shh.

312
00:21:59,050 --> 00:22:00,710
- [Colonel] And
how is he a matter?

313
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:02,400
- He is a disgrace to any man

314
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:05,580
who makes a pretext of
being civilized, sir.

315
00:22:05,670 --> 00:22:08,630
He has been seen
executing wounded men.

316
00:22:08,710 --> 00:22:11,670
He has been seen
robbing their corpses

317
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:14,330
for items of no military value.

318
00:22:14,410 --> 00:22:15,460
- So he has.

319
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:20,770
- Colonel, it is our duty
to put a stop to him.

320
00:22:20,860 --> 00:22:22,730
- With what resources?

321
00:22:22,810 --> 00:22:24,290
It took every ounce of blood

322
00:22:24,380 --> 00:22:26,860
to keep the Yankees in
their place yesterday.

323
00:22:26,950 --> 00:22:28,390
We have none to spare.

324
00:22:28,470 --> 00:22:31,950
- He sullies our cause
with murder and cowardice

325
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:34,130
and you propose to
let him go free?

326
00:22:34,220 --> 00:22:37,260
- Preacher, at any other
time it would be my pleasure

327
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:40,310
to place the noose
around his neck myself.

328
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:44,400
But this is not
civilization, this is war.

329
00:22:44,490 --> 00:22:46,450
As long as the Yankees
control that territory,

330
00:22:46,530 --> 00:22:48,930
they must be the
ones to police it.

331
00:22:49,010 --> 00:22:50,930
- He would be just
as happy to Rob US

332
00:22:51,020 --> 00:22:53,060
if we were better supplied.

333
00:22:53,150 --> 00:22:55,370
- We can only pray
for such misfortunes.

334
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:57,020
[Colonel winces]

335
00:22:57,110 --> 00:23:00,200
Miss, you would pay attention
to your duties, please.

336
00:23:00,290 --> 00:23:02,810
- Another harvest of corpses.

337
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:05,160
- They engage again tomorrow.

338
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:08,210
[Boom vibrating]

339
00:23:17,260 --> 00:23:19,960
[Exciting music]

340
00:23:24,180 --> 00:23:27,570
[Grave robbers chattering]

341
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:33,410
[Dramatic music]

342
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:40,330
[Alan's sister groans]

343
00:23:40,410 --> 00:23:43,370
[Wheel creaking]

344
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:48,730
[Dramatic music]

345
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:59,520
[Cannon creaks]

346
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:03,440
[Men chattering]

347
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:15,230
- Not today, you understand?

348
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,100
Not today.

349
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:21,500
You think this is a bluff?

350
00:24:21,590 --> 00:24:24,020
You can't make it around
before the federals arrive.

351
00:24:24,110 --> 00:24:24,890
Turn back.

352
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:27,460
Turn back!

353
00:24:28,850 --> 00:24:29,590
Turn back and you'll-

354
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:30,770
[gun fires]

355
00:24:30,860 --> 00:24:33,210
[She gasps]

356
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:37,820
[Men clapping]

357
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:43,480
[Alan's sister moans]

358
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:45,700
- Take your hands off of me.

359
00:24:48,180 --> 00:24:50,830
[Dramatic music]

360
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:21,780
[Cannon fire booming]

361
00:25:40,620 --> 00:25:42,360
- [Colonel] This should
interest you, preacher.

362
00:25:42,450 --> 00:25:43,970
- Foucher's gang?

363
00:25:44,060 --> 00:25:45,540
- All that's left of it.

364
00:25:45,630 --> 00:25:48,500
Seems they walked right
into a yankee howitzer.

365
00:25:48,590 --> 00:25:50,330
- [Preacher] Lord almighty.

366
00:25:50,410 --> 00:25:52,460
But why is he here?

367
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:54,160
- The vivandiere brought him in.

368
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:57,030
Thought he was one of ours.

369
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,770
I guess you'd say we
have as much obligation

370
00:25:58,860 --> 00:26:00,770
to his soul as any other.

371
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:06,600
[Foreboding music]

372
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:10,080
- Shh.

373
00:26:25,930 --> 00:26:28,760
[Melancholy music]

374
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:38,640
- [Older sister] August
3rd, 1864, dearest sister.

375
00:26:42,510 --> 00:26:44,470
I'm sure know that
times have been hard

376
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:46,380
since your father's death.

377
00:26:46,470 --> 00:26:49,340
[Melancholy music]

378
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:56,170
The state of the war
does not give US hope.

379
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:06,490
[Weapons booming in distance]
[Men yelling]

380
00:27:06,580 --> 00:27:08,060
It would be easier

381
00:27:08,140 --> 00:27:11,890
if you were here.
[Man moans]

382
00:27:13,670 --> 00:27:15,670
[Person screams]

383
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:18,810
We're not sure you
owe the regiment this
sort of attachment.

384
00:27:18,890 --> 00:27:22,070
However, we understand
your choice and.

385
00:27:24,990 --> 00:27:27,600
[Dramatic music]

386
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:30,510
- [Soldier] Hold to the line.

387
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:31,300
March.

388
00:27:31,380 --> 00:27:33,950
[Anxious music]

389
00:27:50,750 --> 00:27:53,710
[Vivandiere whistles]

390
00:27:55,230 --> 00:27:58,630
[Rain pattering]
[Thunder booming]

391
00:27:58,720 --> 00:27:59,630
- Uh, what?

392
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:12,600
I don't understand.

393
00:28:15,730 --> 00:28:17,340
- How do you feel, soldier?

394
00:28:17,430 --> 00:28:18,690
- Cold, very cold.

395
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:23,090
- I know, you're feverish,
but you're out of the woods.

396
00:28:23,170 --> 00:28:25,260
The colonel needs
to see you now.

397
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:28,530
- Colonel, who's,
who's the colonel?

398
00:28:28,610 --> 00:28:32,140
- Watch him, don't
let him move that leg.

399
00:28:32,230 --> 00:28:33,620
[Thunder echoing]

400
00:28:33,710 --> 00:28:35,840
- Son, this will not wait.

401
00:28:35,930 --> 00:28:39,580
- You? You're, i'm
in reb country?

402
00:28:39,670 --> 00:28:41,450
- Yes, and safe.

403
00:28:41,540 --> 00:28:42,800
Now they found you
near the railroad-

404
00:28:42,890 --> 00:28:44,540
- god damn rebs.

405
00:28:44,630 --> 00:28:46,110
Damn rebs.

406
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:48,330
- They found you near
the railroad track.

407
00:28:48,420 --> 00:28:49,240
You might've seen-

408
00:28:49,330 --> 00:28:50,290
- I shouldn't be here.

409
00:28:50,380 --> 00:28:51,770
I shouldn't be here.

410
00:28:51,860 --> 00:28:53,550
- Do the Yankees have
a railhead there?

411
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,550
We need to know.

412
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:55,550
- No, I'm leaving.

413
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,640
I'm leaving.

414
00:28:57,340 --> 00:28:58,210
Take your hands off me.

415
00:28:58,300 --> 00:28:59,600
Take your hands off me!

416
00:28:59,690 --> 00:29:01,520
[Vivandiere moans]
[Items clattering]

417
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:02,300
[Soldier moans]

418
00:29:02,390 --> 00:29:03,480
- He's bleeding.

419
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:04,390
He's bleeding bad.

420
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,780
- Miss, get up.

421
00:29:05,870 --> 00:29:07,170
Do not let this man die.

422
00:29:07,260 --> 00:29:09,790
[Soldier moaning]
[Liquid sloshing]

423
00:29:09,870 --> 00:29:12,180
- Chloroform? This
will put US all out.

424
00:29:12,270 --> 00:29:13,350
- We cannot move him.

425
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:16,530
[Heartbeat pounding]

426
00:29:16,620 --> 00:29:18,710
[Soldier moaning]

427
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:21,710
[Muffled speaking]

428
00:29:26,370 --> 00:29:27,590
[Heartbeat pounding]

429
00:29:27,670 --> 00:29:29,590
- I can't stop it.

430
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:33,240
[Heartbeat pounding faster]

431
00:29:45,470 --> 00:29:47,650
[Anxious music]

432
00:29:47,740 --> 00:29:50,350
[Alan whistling]

433
00:29:53,830 --> 00:29:54,830
- How about that?

434
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:57,360
We get to ride in style.

435
00:29:57,440 --> 00:30:00,620
They tell me you're the
only reason I'm alive.

436
00:30:00,710 --> 00:30:01,620
Twice over.

437
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:05,930
You are something, magnificent.

438
00:30:07,190 --> 00:30:10,110
- [Older soldier] You all do
your best there, Carolina.

439
00:30:10,190 --> 00:30:13,760
Why, we can't hardly get that
gal to say two words in a row.

440
00:30:13,850 --> 00:30:14,940
- Maybe you Missouri
boys need someone

441
00:30:15,030 --> 00:30:17,380
to show you how it's done.

442
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,810
Tell me something else.

443
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:22,030
Do I also have this,
to thank you for?

444
00:30:23,690 --> 00:30:24,470
Why me?

445
00:30:26,950 --> 00:30:28,390
- [Older soldier]
Y'all will meet up

446
00:30:28,470 --> 00:30:31,080
with your compatriots
soon enough, Carolina.

447
00:30:31,170 --> 00:30:33,650
Word is 21st north Carolina,

448
00:30:34,610 --> 00:30:35,780
they alls just a waiting for US

449
00:30:35,870 --> 00:30:37,870
at the end of this here march.

450
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,610
- Maybe I should stay
close to this lady,

451
00:30:39,700 --> 00:30:40,660
it seems healthier.

452
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:42,100
[Older soldier chuckles]

453
00:30:42,180 --> 00:30:43,790
- [Older soldier]
You Carolina boys.

454
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:46,140
[Tense music]

455
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,670
[Vivandiere coughs]

456
00:30:55,760 --> 00:31:00,160
- Oh, miss, a little late
for you to be out isn't it?

457
00:31:03,770 --> 00:31:08,730
Ah, miss, you don't have
to waste that stuff on me.

458
00:31:08,820 --> 00:31:09,600
I-

459
00:31:10,820 --> 00:31:12,730
so, matches, matches.

460
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:16,870
[Tense music]

461
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,520
[Solder panting]

462
00:31:18,610 --> 00:31:21,270
[Dramatic music]

463
00:31:30,710 --> 00:31:33,150
[Wind blowing]

464
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:44,110
[Gentle music]

465
00:31:50,860 --> 00:31:52,950
- I asked before, why me?

466
00:32:00,350 --> 00:32:01,170
God, keep you.

467
00:32:01,260 --> 00:32:03,960
[Gentle music]

468
00:32:11,970 --> 00:32:13,970
[Weapon explodes]

469
00:32:14,060 --> 00:32:16,970
[Muffled scream]

470
00:32:19,060 --> 00:32:21,930
[Men yelling]

471
00:32:22,020 --> 00:32:24,630
[Guns firing]

472
00:32:31,810 --> 00:32:32,810
[Fire crackling]

473
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:34,210
[Chaotic music]

474
00:32:34,290 --> 00:32:36,910
[Men yelling]

475
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:48,960
[Metal jangling]

476
00:32:50,090 --> 00:32:51,790
- There's no railhead
there you said.

477
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:53,010
No such thing.

478
00:32:54,970 --> 00:32:57,060
What then may I ask is that?

479
00:33:00,630 --> 00:33:01,450
- I was wrong.

480
00:33:01,540 --> 00:33:03,540
I didn't know where I was.

481
00:33:04,980 --> 00:33:06,720
[Alan yelps]

482
00:33:06,810 --> 00:33:08,980
You lie to me again you'll
get worse than that.

483
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:11,810
There's men dead today
didn't need to be.

484
00:33:11,900 --> 00:33:12,900
And how is it you were found

485
00:33:12,990 --> 00:33:16,030
practically inside yankee lines?

486
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:18,300
What were you doing there?

487
00:33:21,990 --> 00:33:22,780
Well?

488
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:25,740
- I refuse to answer.

489
00:33:26,690 --> 00:33:27,910
- [Colonel] What's that?

490
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,180
- That's my choice.

491
00:33:29,260 --> 00:33:31,000
I refuse to answer.

492
00:33:34,010 --> 00:33:35,830
[Alan yelps]

493
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:38,010
- Stop it, that's enough.

494
00:33:39,620 --> 00:33:43,020
- He stayed behind with
the yankee wounded.

495
00:33:43,890 --> 00:33:45,500
- Miss, who is he?

496
00:33:46,710 --> 00:33:48,760
- This is my brother.

497
00:33:48,850 --> 00:33:50,330
- Your brother?

498
00:33:50,410 --> 00:33:54,330
- Private Alan Healy, 10th
Ohio United States army.

499
00:33:55,980 --> 00:33:58,340
He is a wounded prisoner.

500
00:33:58,420 --> 00:34:00,120
I demand you let me treat him.

501
00:34:00,210 --> 00:34:01,510
- Put him under guard.

502
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:02,990
- Colonel, he is a
wounded prisoner.

503
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:04,820
- Prisoner he is, miss.

504
00:34:04,910 --> 00:34:06,470
But two days ago,
private Alan Healy

505
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:09,220
was brought to our
bosom wearing gray

506
00:34:09,300 --> 00:34:11,000
and yesterday,
private Alan Healy

507
00:34:11,090 --> 00:34:14,830
used those false pretenses
to give US false information.

508
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,310
And if private Alan
Healy cannot give

509
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:19,310
a good account of himself
at his trial tomorrow,

510
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:20,490
he will hang.

511
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:25,750
[Ominous music]

512
00:34:37,980 --> 00:34:40,810
[Wind rustling]

513
00:34:45,120 --> 00:34:47,600
- [Alan's sister] My brother.

514
00:34:48,650 --> 00:34:51,910
[Muffled explosion booming]

515
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:53,740
[Explosion booming]

516
00:34:53,830 --> 00:34:56,350
[Man screaming]

517
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:59,180
- [Alan's sister]
This is my brother.

518
00:34:59,270 --> 00:35:00,750
- [Mother] Bring him back.

519
00:35:00,830 --> 00:35:02,400
[Metal twanging]

520
00:35:02,490 --> 00:35:06,230
[Vivandiere breathes heavily]

521
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:10,970
[Dramatic music]

522
00:35:35,210 --> 00:35:40,180
[Vivandiere cries]
[Crickets chirping]

523
00:36:11,340 --> 00:36:13,080
- [Older sister] Dearest sister,

524
00:36:13,170 --> 00:36:16,520
we have had some hard
decisions forced upon US.

525
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:18,520
The loss of our property
was regrettable,

526
00:36:18,610 --> 00:36:20,960
but inevitable given the decline

527
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:23,700
and faced without adequate help.

528
00:36:23,780 --> 00:36:26,350
We will write to you as
soon as we're settled

529
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:28,960
and trust that anything
addressed to the regiment

530
00:36:29,050 --> 00:36:31,140
will find you before long.

531
00:36:31,230 --> 00:36:34,100
[Melancholy music]

532
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:13,530
[Dramatic music]

533
00:37:27,150 --> 00:37:30,200
[Vivandiere coughs]

534
00:37:30,290 --> 00:37:31,810
- Am I needed?

535
00:37:31,900 --> 00:37:32,640
Miss?

536
00:37:34,330 --> 00:37:35,290
- Leave her.

537
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:37,210
Leave her.

538
00:37:38,340 --> 00:37:39,990
I know her.

539
00:37:40,080 --> 00:37:41,730
She is from my town.

540
00:37:42,910 --> 00:37:44,300
I remember when
she was this high.

541
00:37:44,390 --> 00:37:46,780
- Miss, he rarely drinks.

542
00:37:46,870 --> 00:37:48,300
It's only after a battle.

543
00:37:48,390 --> 00:37:51,570
- Your father remarried
before the war.

544
00:37:51,660 --> 00:37:53,130
Isn't that right?

545
00:37:54,090 --> 00:37:55,620
I was glad of that.

546
00:37:56,750 --> 00:38:00,230
I always felt a
little sorry for you.

547
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:02,270
You were so quiet.

548
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,580
- He's not a spy.

549
00:38:05,710 --> 00:38:08,540
He was not awake when I
put him in that uniform.

550
00:38:08,630 --> 00:38:10,940
He did not know till later.

551
00:38:12,110 --> 00:38:14,200
I should not have
done that, I know it.

552
00:38:14,290 --> 00:38:16,380
But his sister she.

553
00:38:16,460 --> 00:38:20,290
[Vivandiere breathes raggedly]

554
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:22,510
She helped me.

555
00:38:23,470 --> 00:38:27,210
The day Josiah died
we could not save him,

556
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:28,650
but she helped me.

557
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:33,570
I knew who he was
when I saw him.

558
00:38:33,650 --> 00:38:35,480
It was in his face.

559
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:40,050
I could not send him
back to her that way.

560
00:38:40,140 --> 00:38:41,180
- Well, surely his own side-

561
00:38:41,270 --> 00:38:42,920
- he would've died.

562
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:45,360
He would've died.

563
00:38:45,450 --> 00:38:47,360
I could not leave him.

564
00:38:47,450 --> 00:38:50,060
[Gentle music]

565
00:38:50,150 --> 00:38:52,670
- He was in a tight spot.

566
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:54,720
What could he do?

567
00:38:54,810 --> 00:38:58,810
We started pressing him
with all those questions.

568
00:38:58,900 --> 00:39:01,070
What could he say?

569
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:05,030
You can't deny what he told
US might've dodged a battle-

570
00:39:05,120 --> 00:39:06,560
- he will not hang.

571
00:39:08,250 --> 00:39:10,170
That is my promise.

572
00:39:10,260 --> 00:39:11,780
He will not hang.

573
00:39:14,350 --> 00:39:16,740
Now, go back to your duties.

574
00:39:18,260 --> 00:39:19,310
Go on.

575
00:39:36,760 --> 00:39:38,810
- Mercy is such a rarity.

576
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:42,590
- I am an old beast.

577
00:39:45,070 --> 00:39:46,200
That is another promise,

578
00:39:46,290 --> 00:39:48,340
I will not be able to keep.

579
00:39:54,300 --> 00:39:56,340
- That would be a cruelty.

580
00:39:56,430 --> 00:40:00,440
- Preacher, she has
already been cruelly used.

581
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:04,700
He knew names from the 21st.

582
00:40:04,790 --> 00:40:07,360
He knew their movements.

583
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:08,970
He came prepared.

584
00:40:09,050 --> 00:40:10,580
- She might've told him.

585
00:40:10,660 --> 00:40:12,190
- That child?

586
00:40:12,270 --> 00:40:13,880
No, preacher.

587
00:40:13,970 --> 00:40:15,840
No, I know her, remember?

588
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:20,020
She did not furnish
those details.

589
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:23,500
And now our provocateur

590
00:40:23,590 --> 00:40:28,330
and that accessory of his
have bent her to their will.

591
00:40:28,420 --> 00:40:30,940
She may have helped her brother,

592
00:40:31,030 --> 00:40:34,430
but they are certainly
presuming on it now.

593
00:40:36,470 --> 00:40:38,820
- What is it you propose to do?

594
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:42,300
- We are naive to think

595
00:40:42,390 --> 00:40:45,050
that there are not more like him

596
00:40:45,130 --> 00:40:47,350
this close to yankee territory.

597
00:40:48,750 --> 00:40:51,310
Mercy is a chance
we cannot take.

598
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:59,320
[Uplifting music]

599
00:41:04,540 --> 00:41:09,290
This court having found private
Healy guilty of espionage

600
00:41:10,420 --> 00:41:14,510
condemns him to hang
by the neck until dead.

601
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:17,770
Sentence to be carried
out immediately.

602
00:41:18,860 --> 00:41:20,430
My god have mercy on his soul.

603
00:41:20,520 --> 00:41:22,910
[Soldiers chanting]

604
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,520
- No, no, you are not his judge.

605
00:41:27,390 --> 00:41:28,700
You have no right!

606
00:41:28,790 --> 00:41:30,530
You broke a promise!

607
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:35,100
Keep your word, damn you!

608
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:38,970
Damn you!
[Gun fires]

609
00:41:39,060 --> 00:41:40,540
- Enough, enough.

610
00:41:40,620 --> 00:41:42,320
Get this girl to
the surgeon's tent.

611
00:41:42,410 --> 00:41:43,840
- Let me go with her.

612
00:41:43,930 --> 00:41:46,500
Please, let me stay with her.

613
00:41:46,590 --> 00:41:48,410
Escort this man.

614
00:41:48,500 --> 00:41:51,420
We'll send for him
when we're ready.

615
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,420
[She groans]

616
00:42:02,650 --> 00:42:05,260
- We have other business, sir.

617
00:42:09,430 --> 00:42:12,260
[Frantic music]

618
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:17,090
[Train bell clanging]

619
00:42:21,790 --> 00:42:23,230
- How about it, yank?

620
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:25,970
Let your women do your
fighting for ya, do ya?

621
00:42:26,060 --> 00:42:27,370
[Liquid sloshes]

622
00:42:27,450 --> 00:42:28,710
- [Other guard] They got to.

623
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,760
All they know is
standing in parade

624
00:42:30,850 --> 00:42:33,500
and polishing their bayonets
and waving to the girls.

625
00:42:33,590 --> 00:42:35,850
[Anxious music]

626
00:42:35,940 --> 00:42:39,420
Ranks are so thin, heard they
got petticoats at Shiloh.

627
00:42:39,510 --> 00:42:40,810
[Dramatic music]

628
00:42:40,900 --> 00:42:43,770
[Muffled speaking]

629
00:43:01,530 --> 00:43:03,660
[Train bell clanging]
[Locomotive chugging]

630
00:43:03,750 --> 00:43:06,360
[Men yelling]

631
00:43:08,230 --> 00:43:10,760
[Frantic music]

632
00:43:12,930 --> 00:43:15,540
[Men yelling]

633
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:19,030
- We had a stroke of
luck with this train.

634
00:43:19,110 --> 00:43:21,770
[Dramatic music]

635
00:43:28,990 --> 00:43:33,520
And now with the bridge in
hand, we have a rare chance.

636
00:43:33,610 --> 00:43:34,950
- [Sentry] Hey, you!

637
00:43:35,040 --> 00:43:37,390
[Dramatic music]
[Train bell clanging]

638
00:43:37,480 --> 00:43:40,660
[Locomotive chugging]

639
00:43:43,700 --> 00:43:46,880
[Train whistle toots]

640
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:06,590
- What the hell are you doing

641
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:09,900
stepping in front of
the train like that?

642
00:44:09,990 --> 00:44:12,430
[Man groans]

643
00:44:14,470 --> 00:44:17,520
[Pole clatters]

644
00:44:17,610 --> 00:44:19,740
[Engineer groans]

645
00:44:19,830 --> 00:44:23,000
[Train whistle blows]

646
00:44:27,530 --> 00:44:30,050
- That one, all the way forward.

647
00:44:31,790 --> 00:44:33,270
[Steam hisses]

648
00:44:33,360 --> 00:44:34,450
Now that one.

649
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:40,450
Too much, too much.

650
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:50,730
- Stop that train!

651
00:44:56,300 --> 00:44:57,340
[Soldier groans]

652
00:44:57,430 --> 00:44:58,120
Get the horses.

653
00:44:58,210 --> 00:44:58,910
Get after them.

654
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:00,430
[Horses neighing]

655
00:45:00,520 --> 00:45:01,560
Lieutenant colonel,
run to the telegraph.

656
00:45:01,650 --> 00:45:02,520
Block the line.

657
00:45:02,610 --> 00:45:05,350
[Upbeat music]

658
00:45:08,610 --> 00:45:11,310
[Dramatic music]

659
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:12,700
- What is she doing?

660
00:45:12,790 --> 00:45:14,450
- Just don't get in her way.

661
00:45:14,530 --> 00:45:17,190
[Dramatic music]

662
00:45:47,830 --> 00:45:48,610
- Ride.

663
00:45:48,700 --> 00:45:51,610
[Dramatic music]

664
00:46:30,740 --> 00:46:33,350
[Tense music]

665
00:47:11,740 --> 00:47:14,650
[Dramatic music]

666
00:47:35,850 --> 00:47:36,890
Miss.

667
00:47:45,940 --> 00:47:48,430
[Fire crackling]

668
00:47:48,510 --> 00:47:50,820
Peel off, boys, peel off.

669
00:47:50,910 --> 00:47:52,910
- That'll go off any second.

670
00:47:53,870 --> 00:47:55,430
- She did it for a reason.

671
00:47:55,520 --> 00:47:58,130
[Dramatic music]

672
00:48:18,460 --> 00:48:19,240
Let's go!

673
00:48:21,760 --> 00:48:25,510
[Locomotive chugging]

674
00:48:25,590 --> 00:48:26,330
No!

675
00:48:30,820 --> 00:48:35,780
[Gentle music]
[Fire crackling]

676
00:48:42,000 --> 00:48:45,050
[Horse hoofs pounding]

677
00:48:52,400 --> 00:48:54,840
[Metal clanks]

678
00:49:13,120 --> 00:49:15,900
[Explosion booms]

679
00:49:22,210 --> 00:49:25,000
[Metal screeches]

680
00:49:41,020 --> 00:49:43,500
[Bell ringing]

681
00:49:49,420 --> 00:49:52,460
[Man whistling tune]

682
00:50:07,960 --> 00:50:11,130
- Excuse me, is
your mother around?

683
00:50:12,220 --> 00:50:15,090
- Ma's not seeing
anyone right now.

684
00:50:15,180 --> 00:50:17,920
- Well, Josiah,
we can always ask.

685
00:50:18,010 --> 00:50:19,880
What is your name, sir?

686
00:50:19,970 --> 00:50:21,270
[Foreboding music]

687
00:50:21,360 --> 00:50:24,320
I, I do not think
she will see you.

688
00:50:25,450 --> 00:50:26,970
[Ominous music]
[Gun trigger clicks]

689
00:50:27,060 --> 00:50:28,890
Josiah, get inside, now.

690
00:50:28,980 --> 00:50:30,940
- Nonsense, nonsense.

691
00:50:33,020 --> 00:50:37,860
Here, that is a
bonafide Jefferson
Davis dime, young fella.

692
00:50:38,940 --> 00:50:40,950
Your ma ever show
you one of those?

693
00:50:41,030 --> 00:50:44,990
Once coin of the realm,
now as rare as hen's teeth.

694
00:50:46,690 --> 00:50:50,870
- Do not think you can scare
me with this child at stake.

695
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:54,650
- How much do you
want him to see?

696
00:50:54,740 --> 00:50:57,880
[Crow cawing]

697
00:50:57,960 --> 00:51:00,100
- Won't you come inside, sir?

698
00:51:03,360 --> 00:51:06,670
[Doors rumbling]

699
00:51:06,750 --> 00:51:09,100
- It'll be just a minute, sir.

700
00:51:14,810 --> 00:51:16,070
She will see you.

701
00:51:18,420 --> 00:51:19,850
What is this?

702
00:51:19,940 --> 00:51:22,550
- You've done well for
yourself, Mr. Healy.

703
00:51:22,640 --> 00:51:24,730
It made you easy to find.

704
00:51:26,770 --> 00:51:28,860
What I want has
nothing to do with him.

705
00:51:28,950 --> 00:51:30,820
- Then let him leave.

706
00:51:30,910 --> 00:51:32,260
- Auntie, the coffee's ready.

707
00:51:32,340 --> 00:51:34,960
- Take a seat, Mr. Healy, now.

708
00:51:44,570 --> 00:51:47,190
[Doors rumbling]

709
00:51:49,970 --> 00:51:52,450
[Crutch taps]

710
00:51:52,540 --> 00:51:56,460
Mrs. Healy, you've had a
rough time of it lately.

711
00:51:57,890 --> 00:52:00,500
- A horse threw
her, two days ago.

712
00:52:01,420 --> 00:52:03,510
- The boy can go.

713
00:52:03,590 --> 00:52:06,420
- [Josiah] The
coffee's ready, ma.

714
00:52:07,600 --> 00:52:10,470
- Mrs. Healy, do
you understand me?

715
00:52:10,560 --> 00:52:11,990
The boy can go.

716
00:52:12,080 --> 00:52:13,730
- You should leave.

717
00:52:13,820 --> 00:52:16,080
This will not profit you.

718
00:52:16,170 --> 00:52:19,040
- I have no interest
in you or you,

719
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:21,610
only the betrayer.

720
00:52:23,740 --> 00:52:25,920
I will have words
with you first.

721
00:52:26,010 --> 00:52:28,050
They are 12 years coming.

722
00:52:29,450 --> 00:52:32,140
[Cup clatters]

723
00:52:44,550 --> 00:52:47,030
You should let the boy leave.

724
00:52:51,470 --> 00:52:53,560
Why don't you let him leave?

725
00:52:53,640 --> 00:52:55,120
Tell her, go on.

726
00:52:55,210 --> 00:52:56,470
- [Alan's sister] Never.

727
00:52:56,560 --> 00:52:59,040
- [Alan] We do not
get in her way.

728
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:04,090
- So that is how you want it?

729
00:53:05,830 --> 00:53:06,610
Fine.

730
00:53:08,310 --> 00:53:10,400
There are boys who've
seen worse than he will,

731
00:53:10,490 --> 00:53:13,230
when they were
younger than he is.

732
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:17,880
This is your last chance.

733
00:53:24,590 --> 00:53:27,240
- Josiah, would
you like a treat?

734
00:53:29,160 --> 00:53:31,120
Here's what you need to do.

735
00:53:31,200 --> 00:53:35,160
Stand up, face that wall
and cover your ears.

736
00:53:35,250 --> 00:53:39,080
Then you'll hear a very loud
noise like papa's shotgun.

737
00:53:39,170 --> 00:53:43,170
If you don't flinch or cry
or turn around before I tell,

738
00:53:43,260 --> 00:53:44,960
you'll get a treat.

739
00:53:46,130 --> 00:53:47,830
Do you understand?

740
00:53:49,050 --> 00:53:52,570
If you can do that, all
will be well, I promise.

741
00:54:13,420 --> 00:54:18,120
Colonel, gunner foucher never
met the Yankees that day.

742
00:54:19,120 --> 00:54:20,120
He, met, me.

743
00:54:24,730 --> 00:54:26,210
Now is your moment.

744
00:54:30,170 --> 00:54:31,960
[Glasses pinging]

745
00:54:32,050 --> 00:54:34,570
[Tense music]

746
00:54:34,660 --> 00:54:37,270
[Trigger clicks]

747
00:54:38,530 --> 00:54:41,230
[Dramatic music]

748
00:54:50,500 --> 00:54:55,460
[Gun fires]
[Glass shatters]

749
00:54:56,370 --> 00:54:57,160
- Ma?

750
00:55:03,210 --> 00:55:06,170
- Darling, take him
into the kitchen.

751
00:55:06,250 --> 00:55:08,260
We'll handle things in here.

752
00:55:08,340 --> 00:55:10,480
- No, you take him.

753
00:55:10,560 --> 00:55:12,260
This is our job.

754
00:55:12,350 --> 00:55:13,650
- I want to stay.

755
00:55:13,740 --> 00:55:17,090
- Josie, you can't,
someone's hurt.

756
00:55:17,180 --> 00:55:19,220
- I know, I want to stay.

757
00:55:24,840 --> 00:55:27,580
[Colonel moaning]

758
00:55:27,670 --> 00:55:30,670
- [Alan's sister] It's a
winging more than anything.

759
00:55:30,760 --> 00:55:32,500
He has a chance.

760
00:55:32,580 --> 00:55:34,280
- Can we fix him?

761
00:55:34,370 --> 00:55:36,850
- Are you fearless
today, little Josie?

762
00:55:36,940 --> 00:55:37,980
Maybe we can.

763
00:55:42,070 --> 00:55:44,510
Like as not, cracked a few ribs.

764
00:55:46,160 --> 00:55:50,250
Right now, it's the bleeding
we have to worry about.

765
00:55:50,340 --> 00:55:54,210
- [Vivandiere] You take
this, keep his head down.

766
00:55:54,300 --> 00:55:55,610
- Yeah, you traitors.

767
00:55:55,690 --> 00:55:58,090
You vile turncoats.

768
00:55:58,180 --> 00:55:59,660
What have you done to me?

769
00:55:59,740 --> 00:56:03,620
Joe-fired adventuresses,
what have you done to me?

770
00:56:03,700 --> 00:56:04,440
- Shh.

771
00:56:07,790 --> 00:56:10,270
[Gentle music]

